# migrated from tests/cases/counterfactual.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test counterfactual]
# gen128 (L20-deep): COUNTERFACTUAL meta-reasoning — the reflexive closure of
# mod_strategy. gen105 reported the real trace ("why did you answer that way?").
# This answers "what would you have said WITHOUT module X?" and it does not
# confabulate: it RE-RUNS its own first-match-wins dispatch over the previous
# turn with one module suppressed, and reports whatever its alternative self
# actually computes. A deterministic C program simulating itself with a part
# removed — introspection-as-method become introspection-as-feature (PRINCIPLES).

# Guard: there is no previous turn to reconsider yet.
> what would you have said without arith?
< I don't have a previous turn to reconsider yet.

# Establish a real turn: arith computes it.
> what is 2 plus 2?
< 4.

# "what else could have answered?" suppresses the actual WINNER (arith) and
# re-dispatches. The honest, slightly humbling result: arith is parrot0's only
# arithmetic faculty for this phrasing, so nothing else matches — it would fall
# back. This is COMPUTED by re-simulation, not asserted.
> what else could have answered?
< Without 'arith', nothing else matches — I'd fall back to "I don't understand that yet."

# Suppressing a NON-winner changes nothing: arith still ran first. The system
# knows the difference because it actually re-ran the control flow.
> what would you have said without symbolic?
< Setting 'symbolic' aside changes nothing — 'arith' ran first anyway and still answers "4."

# It will only set aside a module it really has (grounded in the registry).
> what would you have said without the frobnicator module?
< I don't have a module called "frobnicator" to set aside.

# A genuine ALTERNATIVE SELF: 'haha' is claimed by the affective 'social'
# register; with social set aside, the 'chitchat' register catches it — a
# different real faculty, its reply produced by re-simulation, not a stored line.
> haha
< :) Glad you're enjoying the conversation.
> what would you have said without social?
< Without 'social', the next module that matches is 'chitchat', and it would answer "Ha, you're playful! Ask me something?"

